HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 214
BY REPRESENTATIVE BAYHAM
A RESOLUTION
To commend Sabrina Schmidt for her artistic contributions to the cultural landscape of
St. Bernard Parish and the state of Louisiana.
WHEREAS, Sabrina Schmidt grew up in the Delacroix Island community in
St. Bernard Parish, Louisiana, where she developed a lifelong passion for art; and
WHEREAS, Sabrina received a formal education in art and design and began work
as a web designer early in her professional career; in the wake of Hurricane Katrina, she
moved to Tennessee and found new inspiration in the mountain scenery; and
WHEREAS, Sabrina is incredibly talented with a brush and paint, and she has
developed her own style of plein air art; and
WHEREAS, as a plein air oil painter, Sabrina connects deeply with her surroundings
and focuses on light, atmosphere, and subject matter; her art captures the emotional essence
of a landscape through exploration, connection, and design; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Schmidt earned the Best in Show award at her first plein air festival
in 2022 and has since received recognition at regional and national events; she won Best in
Show, Artist Choice, and Best Main Street at a 2025 plein air event in West Reading,
Pennsylvania; she also won Artist Choice and Best in Show at Teche Plein Air in 2026; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Schmidt was one of ten artists selected for the Art in the Park: En
Plein Air Public Arts Project in New Orleans; she also designed and painted the official
artwork for two consecutive Grand Isle Fishing Rodeos, which is the oldest fishing
competition in the United States, and she created the poster for the 50th Anniversary
Louisiana Crawfish Festival in 2025; and
